00:28:44,580 --> 00:28:47,080
You are just generating cognitive exhaust.

473
00:28:47,220 --> 00:28:47,580
Wow.

474
00:28:47,900 --> 00:28:52,500
I know exactly what that feels like when I'm arguing in circles or just staring at a blank page.

475
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:57,260
It's a deeply frustrating cognitive state, and the geometry maps it perfectly.

476
00:28:57,260 --> 00:29:05,440
But the paper goes even deeper into the mechanics of this movement, addressing a fundamental paradox in neuroscience.

477
00:29:05,780 --> 00:29:06,600
What's the paradox?

